{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"54657134-7a9a-43ec-8bbe-7d653baed56e","content":"Use `dotnet watch test` with the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nThis will:\n- **`dotnet watch test`** — re-run tests automatically when you save a file\n- **`--filter \"FullyQualifiedName~...\"`** — only run tests whose name contains that string\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so you don't need the full namespace. You can also filter by just the method name:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"Name=ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f4d3a27d-374c-4043-b62c-2aa5c3664fea","outputTokens":163,"requestId":"4C55:3988B0:CBA3F8:FB2803:6A01345A"},"id":"cedd8fe2-91c2-45b7-8506-0cfb1727e63e","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:44:00.543Z","parentId":"895f3aa5-7103-4d73-a530-4f9023cb1468"}
